Portuguese

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
 
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /aw.kiˈla(ʁ)/ [aʊ̯.kiˈla(h)]
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /aw.kiˈla(ʁ)/ [aʊ̯.kiˈla(h)]
    • (São Paulo) IPA(key): /aw.kiˈla(ɾ)/ [aʊ̯.kiˈla(ɾ)]
    • (Rio de Janeiro) IPA(key): /aw.kiˈla(ʁ)/ [aʊ̯.kiˈla(χ)]
    • (Southern Brazil) IPA(key): /aw.kiˈla(ɻ)/ [aʊ̯.kiˈla(ɻ)]
 
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /al.kiˈlaɾ/ [aɫ.kiˈlaɾ]
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /al.kiˈlaɾ/ [aɫ.kiˈlaɾ]
    • (Southern Portugal) IPA(key): /al.kiˈla.ɾi/ [aɫ.kiˈla.ɾi]

  • Hyphenation: al‧qui‧lar

Etymology 1

[edit]

From alquila (“alkyl”) +‎ -ar.

Verb

[edit]

alquilar (first-person singular present alquilo, first-person singular preterite alquilei, past participle alquilado)

  1. (organic chemistry) to alkylate (to add an alkyl group to a compound)

Etymology 2

[edit]

From alquilé (“beast-of-burden rental”) +‎ -ar.

Verb

[edit]

alquilar (first-person singular present alquilo, first-person singular preterite alquilei, past participle alquilado)

  1. to rent or hire (a horse or person) for transportation

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From alquiler (“rent”).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /alkiˈlaɾ/ [al.kiˈlaɾ]
  • Audio (Colombia):(file)
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: al‧qui‧lar

Verb

[edit]

alquilar (first-person singular present alquilo, first-person singular preterite alquilé, past participle alquilado)

  1. (transitive) to rent
    Synonym: (Latin America) rentar
  2. (transitive) to rent out something to someone
    Synonyms: (Latin America) rentar, (Latin America) arrendar
